Hereâ€™s whatâ€™s planned for future releases of **AutoEMXSp**:
- âš¡ GPU acceleration for faster spectral fitting
- ðŸ Upgrade to **Python 3.12** for improved performance, modern syntax features, and better compatibility with the latest scientific libraries
- ðŸš€ Integration of a **forked `lmfit`** version accepting `Model.fit(data, fit_kws={'full_output': False})` to avoid covariance computations and speed up fitting
- ðŸ“ New scripts for **spectral parameter calibration** to extend the `XSp_calibs` library to your own instrument.
- ðŸ¤– Integration of ML models for particle segmentation and improved size distribution analysis

